AGI - The dam collapsed in Orsk>, in the Russian Ural area, has yielded due to delays in maintenance. The regional prosecutor's office is investigating the collapse, which caused the flooding of a inhabited center, the evacuation of thousands of people from their homes and also two victims, according to Ria Novosti. "The dam collapsed on 5 April 2024, > because the measures aimed at maintaining in good technical state its hydrotechnical equipment were not taken in time," said the prosecutor.
The structure was set up in 2010. "The branches of the State Technical Supervisory Authority have previously identified breaches in the maintenance of the dam and have been sent notes to the competent authority on this," said the prosecutor's office.
<div </div
&nbsp;
In particular, in the last month the prosecutor sent to the first deputy mayor of Orsk "a warning about the inadmissibility of the violation of the law on the protection of the population and the territories from the situations of natural emergency and caused by man". Two days ago, the state of emergency was declared in the Orenburg region due to the deterioration of the flood situation, 495 temporary accommodation facilities were deployed with a capacity of over 82,300 people. &nbsp;
&nbsp;

